================================================================================
Third-party software
================================================================================

This product includes software developed by third parties. For an exhaustive
list, run `cargo about generate` or inspect `cargo tree -p agiworkforce-cli`.
The most significant direct dependencies are:

- ratatui (MIT) — terminal UI framework
  https://github.com/ratatui-org/ratatui
- crossterm (MIT) — cross-platform terminal manipulation
  https://github.com/crossterm-rs/crossterm
- tokio (MIT) — asynchronous runtime
  https://github.com/tokio-rs/tokio
- reqwest (MIT OR Apache-2.0) — HTTP client
  https://github.com/seanmonstar/reqwest
- serde / serde_json (MIT OR Apache-2.0) — serialization
  https://github.com/serde-rs/serde
- clap (MIT OR Apache-2.0) — CLI argument parsing
  https://github.com/clap-rs/clap
- syntect (MIT) — syntax highlighting
  https://github.com/trishume/syntect
- pulldown-cmark (MIT) — markdown rendering
  https://github.com/raphlinus/pulldown-cmark
- axum / tower / tower-http (MIT) — HTTP server framework (used by mcp-server
  subcommand and the embedded app server)
  https://github.com/tokio-rs/axum
- arboard (MIT OR Apache-2.0) — clipboard access
- cpal / hound (MIT / Apache-2.0) — audio capture (voice mode)
- notify (MIT OR Artistic-2.0) — filesystem watching
- nix (MIT) — Unix system calls
- cron (MIT OR Apache-2.0) — cron expression parsing
- rustyline (MIT) — readline-compatible line editor
- dialoguer (MIT) — interactive CLI prompts
- indicatif (MIT) — progress bars
- chrono (MIT OR Apache-2.0) — date/time handling
- regex (MIT OR Apache-2.0) — regular expressions

================================================================================
Reference materials
================================================================================

The codex-cli source preserved at ~/Desktop/reference/codex-cli/ (88 dirs,
Apache-2.0) is consulted as a reference implementation for MCP transport
patterns, plan-mode UX, and sandbox architecture. No code is copied; only API
shapes and protocol patterns are referenced. See
~/.claude/plans/cli-competitive-floor.md for the explicit pattern citations.

================================================================================
Security notice
================================================================================

Until the master-password vault rewire (~/.claude/plans/sprint1-vault-rewire.md)
ships, OAuth tokens and BYOK API keys are stored in ~/.agiworkforce/auth.json
with file mode 0o600. Plain-disk storage is the current security posture; OS
keychain integration is in active development.

For security disclosures, see SECURITY.md (forthcoming).
